{"name": "not-gitmodules", "metadata": {"name": "not-gitmodules", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: Other/Proprietary License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Armen-Jean-Andreasian/not_gitmodules", "license": "Custom License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A library for managing git repositories in a directory.", "upload_time": 1733206957}, "documentation": ["# Not gitmodules\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n# Why this?\r\n\r\n1. This is how simple gitmodules should be. Add and remove modules without caring about irrelevant stuff. No shitshow,\r\n   just simplicity.\r\n2. Production-use friendly. Which is documented in the LISENSE.\r\n3. No third-party libs needed, only built-in tools used.\r\n4. OS-agnostic. Written in Python, which means this can be used in any type of projects that are supposed to run on\r\n   Linux.\r\n\r\n---   \r\n\r\n# Installation\r\n\r\n- Git clone\r\n- Pip install `pip install not-gitmodules`\r\n\r\n---\r\n# Usage\r\n\r\nCreate a `notgitmodules.yaml` file in your root directory\r\n\r\n1. Example with code:\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\nrepos:\r\n  # directory: url (ssh or https)\r\n\r\n  # example\r\n  file_reader: https://github.com/Free-Apps-for-All/file_manager_git_module\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen pass it to `initializer` function:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom not_gitmodules import initializer\r\n\r\ninitializer('/path/to/notgitmodules.yaml')\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Example with CLI\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n--- \r\n\r\n# Possible issues with private repositories\r\n\r\nIf cloning failed, but you have access to the repository, try to provide HTTPS repo-url instead of SSH\r\nin `notgitmodules.yaml`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n# That's it!\r\n\r\nNo more waste of time with index, .git, metadata, which actually offer no trade.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n# Author\r\n\r\nArmen-Jean Andreasian, 2024\r\n\r\n---\r\n# License\r\n\r\nThis project is licensed under the Custom License. See the [LICENSE](./LICENSE) file for details.\r\n\r\n- You may use the project for commercial or personal purposes.\r\n- You may not claim ownership of the project.\r\n\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.clone_repo", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.clone_repo.clone_repo", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "root_dir_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "directory_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Clone the repository into the specified directory."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.move_folder", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.move_folder.move_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "destination", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["** Withdrawn function:\n    Move a folder to a new destination."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.delete_git", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.delete_git.delete_using_subprocess", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.delete_git.drop_read_only", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.delete_git.delete_git_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "directory", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Deletes .git folder from a directory"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.directory_rename", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "not_gitmodules.parts.directory_rename.rename_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name":